The paper deals with regularization of deep convolutional neural networks for image datasets, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a novel stochastic pooling approach, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of dropout, which is a common regularization technique in neural networks and falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
